full_content.content: Common reasons your Whirlpool range broiler is not working
The most common reasons your Whirlpool range broiler is not working are a bad broil element, inoperative electronic control board or a faulty igniter.
We can help! Our service technicians have repaired over
Whirlpool ranges. We can fix yours no matter where you bought it.
Most common repairs needed to fix a Whirlpool range

A broken broil element is a common cause for the broil mode not working in an electric range. Unplug the range or shut off the house circuit breaker to disconnect electrical power. Check the boil element for damage and replace it if it's cracked or broken. If the broil element shorted to the metal inside the oven cavity, it may also have damaged the electronic control board. If the broiler won't work after replacing the broil element, you may also need to replace the electronic control board and any damaged wiring.
How to replace the oven broil element

An inoperative electronic control board can lead to various failures in a range, including a lack of power or heating in the oven or surface element, or prevent the oven from turning off. This is because the board serves as the brain of the range, controlling crucial operations such as regulating oven temperatures, running cooling fans, and controlling cooking time. If the electronic control board malfunctions, it can disrupt communication between many different components. A failing board may cause a chattering or clicking noise from the range and may emit a burning odor. Due to the potential impact on multiple components, it is advisable to have a Sears Home Services professional conduct diagnostic tests on the board to confirm if replacement is necessary.
How to replace a range oven control board

A faulty range igniter can prevent a burner from igniting, resulting in no heat from the bake or broil burner in the oven, or from a surface burner. A failed igniter could also cause difficulty in lighting the burner, requiring multiple attempts to achieve ignition. The igniter may emit a clicking sound without successfully lighting the gas, indicating a malfunction. In some cases, the igniter may not produce any visible spark at all. An igniter failure can lead to delayed ignition, causing a noticeable delay between turning the knob and the burner lighting.
Why is my Whirlpool oven broiler not working?
A broken broil element, failed electronic control board, wiring failure or tripped safety switch can prevent the broiler from working in a Whirlpool electric oven.
Unplug the power cord or shut off the house circuit breaker for the range
and examine the broil element for damage.
Replace the broil element if it’s cracked or broken.
Here’s a safe DIY video that shows how to replace the broil element in a Whirlpool oven:
If you’re not certain that you can safely replace the broil element on your own, schedule
service and we’ll install a new broil element for you.
Whirlpool Gas Oven Broil Burner Troubleshooting
The number cause of a Whirlpool oven broiler failure is a bad igniter. Follow the tips in this video to examine the oven broil burner and igniter to determine the cause of the broiler failure:
The video shows how to troubleshoot a bake burner not igniting but the procedure is the same for a broil burner in a gas range.

These tips should help you fix the broil failure in your Whirlpool range. If you’re unable to find the cause of the problem and fix it on your own, schedule repair service and we’ll send a technician to your home to fix the problem for you.
What to expect when you experience a Whirlpool range broiler not working issue
How is the broiler not working problem fixed?

Correcting most broiler not working problems usually involves replacing the broil element, electronic control board or igniter. However, there are many potential causes, so a thorough diagnosis is key to fixing the problem. An accurate diagnosis is essential to understanding how much the repair will be.
Sears Home Services recommendations for a range broiler that is not working

When the range broiler is not working it can be for many reasons. To avoid replacing unneeded parts we recommend having a Sears Home Services professional perform diagnostic tests to identify the root cause of the problem. Our technicians are experienced at diagnosing all types of range failures; if you're in need of
, they can quickly determine the issue and make the necessary repairs.
What to look out for with a range broiler not working diagnosis

Diagnosing modern appliances without proper knowledge and training can be difficult. Without using proper diagnostic techniques, fixing your range problem will only be achieved through changing parts on a hunch. Appliances, especially in the last 10 years, have become extremely advanced, and many models have electronic parts that are difficult to test. DIY repairs on the latest appliance models are becoming increasingly difficult.

full_content.content: Why isn’t the broiler on my Whirlpool range working?
A faulty broiler element, malfunctioning control board, or broken thermostat could prevent the broiler from working. Inspect these components for damage or faults.
Could a faulty broiler element prevent my Whirlpool range broiler from working?
Yes, if the broiler element is broken, it will prevent the broiler from heating up. Replacing the broiler element should resolve the issue.
How can I fix my Whirlpool range if the broiler isn’t working?
Check the broiler element, thermostat, and control board for damage. Replacing any faulty parts should restore broiling functionality.
What should I do if the broiler on my Whirlpool range still isn’t working after replacing the element?
If the broiler continues not to work, the control board or internal wiring may need professional inspection and repair.

Don't let a non-heating gas oven ruin your day. Follow these simple troubleshooting steps to get it working.

A convection range is a kitchen appliance that features a convection oven, which uses a fan and exhaust system to circulate hot air around the food, resulting in faster, more even cooking and baking compared to conventional ovens.

A drop-in range is a type of kitchen stove that is designed to be fitted into a pre-existing space in kitchen cabinetry, mounted on a platform, flanked by cabinetry, and often featuring a custom panel at the bottom.
What is a Dual Fuel Range?
A dual fuel range combines the precision of an electric oven with the responsiveness of a gas cooktop, offering the best of both worlds for cooking enthusiasts.
BTU, or British Thermal Unit, measures the amount of heat required to raise the temperature of one pound of water by one degree Fahrenheit.
